summary:
The Security Council, reaffirming previous resolutions and statements on Sudan, and underlining the importance of full compliance with and implementation of these, 
reaffirms its strong commitment to Sudan's sovereignty, unity, independence, and territorial integrity. 
Noting the Special Report of the African Union Commission Chairperson and the UN Secretary-General (S/2019/445), 
determines the situation in Sudan threatens international peace and security. 
Acting under Chapter VII, 
1. Extends UNAMID's mandate until 31 October 2019; 
2. Decides UNAMID will continue implementing its mandate as set out in resolution 2429 (2018) and temporarily extends the drawdown period for military personnel to maintain self-protection capacities; 
3. Requests the Secretary-General to provide an oral update within 60 days and a Special Report by 30 September 2019, with the African Union Commission Chairperson, on: 
    (i) the situation on the ground and recommendations on UNAMID's drawdown; 
    (ii) a joint African Union-United Nations political strategy for a follow-on mechanism to UNAMID; 
4. Decides to remain seized of the matter.
